# Cursor IDE Rules

## Pre-open Files on Session Start

These files should be opened automatically when starting a new Cursor session to provide immediate context:

- docs/handbook-mount/prompts/cursor/VIBE_CODING_PROMPTS.md
- docs/operator-log.md
- docs/journal/now.md
- docs/handbook-mount/decision-log/ADR-INDEX.md
- docs/seams-invariants.md
- env-template
- docs/architecture/tldr.md
- docs/roadmap/phase1_milestones.md
- docs/contracts/trade_v1.md
- docs/handbook-mount/docs/index.md

## File Priority

High-signal documentation for quick reference and planning:
1. Development guidelines (handbook-mount/prompts/cursor/VIBE_CODING_PROMPTS.md)
2. Operator log (operator-log.md)
3. Current status (journal/now.md)
4. Architectural decisions (handbook-mount/decision-log/ADR-INDEX.md)
5. Non-negotiables (seams-invariants.md)
6. Environment setup (env-template)
7. Architecture overview (architecture/tldr.md)
8. Development roadmap (roadmap/phase1_milestones.md)
9. API contracts (contracts/trade_v1.md)
10. External documentation mount point (handbook-mount/README.md)
